<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="927" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d927">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.5151/263: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dominian</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-14T18:00:00-05:00">February 14, 1935—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. Please send by airmail the report requested in Department’s
                            instruction No. 309, of January 21, also reporting whether the oil
                            companies have a possibility of obtaining through legal action redress
                            for the alleged discriminations in favor of the State-owned company.
                            What are the prospects of American oil companies arriving at an early
                            satisfactory adjustment of their various difficulties with the
                            Government?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>